    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect subband size calculation in NR PDCCH processing\n\n### Summary\nThe `get_subband_size` function in nr_common.c had incorrect boundary conditions that caused wrong subband size calculations for edge cases. When NPRB values matched the upper bounds of defined ranges (72, 144, 275), the function would incorrectly fall through to the AssertFatal instead of returning the proper subband size.\n\nThis manifested as unexpected termination during PDCCH processing when specific bandwidth configurations were used.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/nr/nr_common.c`: Fixed boundary conditions from `<` to `<=` for proper range handling\n- `common/utils/nr/nr_common.c`: Improved logic flow with explicit if-else structure\n- `common/utils/nr/nr_common.c`: Added explicit return path\n\nTo reproduce: Configure a UE with 72, 144, or 275 PRBs and observe AssertFatal being triggered during PDCCH processing instead of proper subband size calculation.\n"
}